98
00:04:25,859 --> 00:04:29,320
we understand that using that term to prepare for something

99
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,619
has a broad application.

100
00:04:31,619 --> 00:04:34,220
You can prepare for a lot of different things.

101
00:04:34,220 --> 00:04:37,899
And we find that preparation, no doubt, is necessary.

102
00:04:37,899 --> 00:04:39,579
In fact, I could say it this way,

103
00:04:39,579 --> 00:04:42,220
I prepared for the message this morning.

104
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:45,000
I prepared for the message that I'll preach this evening.

105
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,700
Those that taught Sunday school this morning,

106
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,859
they had a measure of preparation.

107
00:04:48,859 --> 00:04:51,579
If you're gonna cook a meal, you have some preparation.

108
00:04:51,579 --> 00:04:54,899
You do some things ahead of time, you prepare.

109
00:04:54,899 --> 00:04:58,660
And we understand that it has a broad application

110
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:01,399
with regard to the subject of preparation.

111
00:05:01,399 --> 00:05:05,660
This morning, contextually from 2 Timothy chapter three,

112
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:09,739
and what we're looking at is preparation for persecution.

113
00:05:09,739 --> 00:05:12,140
Now, as I think about preparation,

114
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:14,899
and I understand that there's a broad category of things,

115
00:05:14,899 --> 00:05:17,140
application in which we could prepare for,

116
00:05:17,140 --> 00:05:19,239
I find this to be true also,

117
00:05:19,239 --> 00:05:23,339
that there are times in which we prepare for something

118
00:05:23,339 --> 00:05:26,820
that we actually hope never comes to pass.

119
00:05:28,299 --> 00:05:30,779
So when I speak about preparation for persecution,

120
00:05:30,779 --> 00:05:32,119
I'm saying prepare for something

121
00:05:32,119 --> 00:05:34,019
that quite honestly tonight,

122
00:05:34,019 --> 00:05:35,980
today, I'll say from this platform,

123
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:38,480
and I believe that you probably would agree with me,

124
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:41,540
I hope that I never have to face persecution.

125
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:44,779
But the reality is that preparation for persecution

126
00:05:44,779 --> 00:05:46,980
is absolutely necessary.

127
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:49,940
And we find that though we would give this morning

128
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:52,059
the instruction that we ought to prepare

129
00:05:52,059 --> 00:05:53,420
for the persecution,

130
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:56,119
that we actually would hope that it never happens.

131
00:05:56,119 --> 00:05:57,559
What do I mean by that?

132
00:05:57,559 --> 00:06:00,700
Well, I lived, as you know, I was born in North Carolina,

133
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,500
I lived a number of years in North Carolina,

134
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,299
and I remember as a young child,

135
00:06:04,299 --> 00:06:06,059
that there are many times in which you had,

136
00:06:06,059 --> 00:06:07,820
during hurricane season,

137
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:09,980
you had the threat of a storm

138
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:11,619
hitting the coast where we lived.

139
00:06:11,619 --> 00:06:14,179
We weren't that far inland where we lived,

140
00:06:14,179 --> 00:06:15,299
and there were several times

141
00:06:15,299 --> 00:06:17,820
in which we had some pretty serious storms

142
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:20,100
that were coming, and the way that they were tracking it

143
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,820
looked like we were gonna get hit.

144
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:23,260
And guess what we did?

145
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:24,820
We made preparation.

146
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:27,880
But in so doing, we made the preparation,

147
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,299
but we also kind of hoped

148
00:06:29,299 --> 00:06:31,260
that the storm wouldn't actually hit us,

149
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:33,779
that we wouldn't deal with all of the damages

150
00:06:33,779 --> 00:06:36,220
from the storm, but we made the preparation.

151
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,059
Why?

152
00:06:37,059 --> 00:06:39,700
In the event that the storm did follow the track

153
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:42,940
that the meteorologist assumed that it would.

154
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:44,459
Now, here's the reality.

155
00:06:44,459 --> 00:06:48,459
When we made the preparation and the storm didn't come,

156
00:06:48,459 --> 00:06:51,299
we weren't disappointed about the fact that we prepared.

157
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,880
You know when you're disappointed if you didn't prepare?

158
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,119
When the storm comes.

159
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:00,339
The storm comes, and you say, you know what?

160
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:02,100
Those guys don't know what they're talking about.

161
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,339
They've said this before,

162
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:05,339
and they've always followed this track,

163
00:07:05,339 --> 00:07:07,859
but it never happens, and we've been spared,

164
00:07:07,859 --> 00:07:10,420
and I'm not gonna waste my time preparing,

165
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:12,660
and then the storm comes, and guess what?

166
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:15,260
You regret that you did not prepare.

167
00:07:16,179 --> 00:07:17,260
In a very real sense,

168
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:18,820
when we talk about the subject this morning

169
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:20,779
of preparation for persecution,

170
00:07:20,779 --> 00:07:23,899
we find that we live and we have lived

171
00:07:23,899 --> 00:07:26,859
in our lifetime here in the United States of America,

172
00:07:26,859 --> 00:07:29,859
we've had great freedom and we've had great privilege.

173
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:32,079
We had 18 that were out on visitation yesterday.

174
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:34,500
We were knocking doors in our community,

175
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:37,260
and we were going out and distributing literature

176
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:39,179
perfectly free to do that.

177
00:07:39,179 --> 00:07:41,299
We had no persecution whatsoever.

178
00:07:41,299 --> 00:07:44,799
There was no one, we have the freedom to do it.

179
00:07:44,799 --> 00:07:46,739
Can I tell you this morning that that's not the case

180
00:07:46,739 --> 00:07:48,559
everywhere around the globe?

181
00:07:48,559 --> 00:07:51,100
There are places this morning around the globe

182
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,619
that they do not have the freedoms that we have,

183
00:07:53,619 --> 00:07:56,100
and they have not had the freedoms that we have,

184
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,739
and by the way, many places around the globe

185
00:07:58,739 --> 00:08:01,640
that once had the freedoms that we enjoy today

186
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:04,880
no longer have those freedoms.

187
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:07,920
You can read in the news about various countries,

188
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,779
you can look at England and Scotland,

189
00:08:09,779 --> 00:08:10,940
and you can look at Canada,

190
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,779
and you can read things that have happened

191
00:08:12,779 --> 00:08:16,220
even in recent weeks where their freedoms

192
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:19,279
are being squeezed and they're not having

193
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:22,579
the level of religious liberty that they once did.

194
00:08:23,859 --> 00:08:28,320
As we think about this idea of preparation for persecution,

195
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:32,880
I hope this morning that if persecution would come to us

196
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:35,119
in the sense in which we're gonna deal with this morning,

197
00:08:35,119 --> 00:08:36,679
that we would be prepared for it

198
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,799
and that we'd be ready to stand.

199
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:41,919
In the face of the opposition, in the face of adversity,

200
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:46,919
that in the evil day, as Ephesians 6 says, we would stand.

201
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:50,539
We find that as Paul is writing to Timothy

202
00:08:50,539 --> 00:08:52,799
and Timothy is ministering in Ephesus,

203
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:55,919
it's interesting that Ephesians 6 deals with

204
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:57,760
all of this instruction with regard

205
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:01,239
to be strong in the Lord, put on the whole armor of God,

206
00:09:01,239 --> 00:09:04,440
and Paul is writing to Timothy about the persecution

207
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:07,039
and preparing for such persecution.

208
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:10,000
I believe this morning that if we fail to prepare

209
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,080
for persecution and persecution comes in your life

210
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,619
and in my life, that two things will be true.

211
00:09:15,619 --> 00:09:18,520
Number one, we will regret not preparing,

212
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,559
and number two, we will be vulnerable

213
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,000
to the attack of the enemy.

214
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,679
And so this morning, we understand

215
00:09:25,679 --> 00:09:28,320
that persecution is nothing new.

216
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:31,080
In fact, if you study in the book of Acts

217
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:34,200
in the fourth chapter, the persecution begins.

218
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:37,520
The church, of course, is born and God is working.

219
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,599
Jesus Christ said, I will build my church

220
00:09:39,599 --> 00:09:41,960
and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it,

221
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,159
but we know that Satan hates the church,

222
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:46,320
Satan hates every child of God,

223
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:49,119
and he's bringing persecution, he's bringing attack,

224
00:09:49,119 --> 00:09:51,700
and what they started to do in Acts chapter number four

225
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,059
is they tried to threaten the people of God

226
00:09:54,059 --> 00:09:56,320
to no longer speak the name of God

227
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,140
nor to preach the word of God,

228
00:09:58,140 --> 00:09:59,940
and we find that as they faced.

229
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:02,060
various levels of persecution,

230
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:05,100
whether that was being incarcerated,

231
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:06,860
whether that was being interrogated,

232
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:09,100
whether that was being beaten or threatened,

233
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:12,780
we find that they faced great levels of persecution.

234
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:14,180
You come to chapter number seven

235
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:16,860
and you find the first martyr of the New Testament church,

236
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:19,740
with Stephen giving his life, and as he preached,

237
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:22,540
and what a message he preached in Acts chapter number seven,

238
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:24,700
he knew the Bible, he knew the scriptures,

239
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:26,720
and he preached a powerful message,

240
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:30,160
and there was great difficulty with regard

241
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,520
to what he faced as those people

242
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,520
that stood there and heard that message.

243
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,080
They were cut to the heart.

244
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,920
They were dealing with the truth

245
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:40,600
that had been given to them,

246
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:44,920
and we find that as they responded with stoning him,

247
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:47,600
and he looks up and he sees

248
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,020
as Jesus would welcome him to heaven,

249
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:51,320
but then in chapter eight,

250
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,200
the persecution rises a whole nother level.

